{{Quote|As you wish, your saber is somewhere in the ruined temple to the South. To find it, you'll need to utilize your primary Force skills.|Luke Skywalker to Kyle Katarn|<ref name="JK:JO">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight II: Jedi Outcast]]''</ref>}}
The '''Yavin training grounds''' was used by the [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] of the [[New Jedi Order]] to hone their skills. A labyrinth of old [[Massassi/Legends|Massassi]] ruins located to the South of the [[Great Temple/Legends|Great Temple]], the training grounds offered Jedi students plenty of opportunity to improve their skills in [[Force jump/Legends|Force Jump]], [[Telekinesis/Legends|Force pull]], [[Telekinesis/Legends|Force push]], and [[Force speed/Legends|Force speed]]. With an inventory of [[Remote/Legends|remotes]] and [[ASP-19 battle droid/Legends|Jedi training droids]], the training grounds also offered opportunities to practice [[Lightsaber combat/Legends|lightsaber combat]].<ref name="JK:JA">''[[Star Wars: Jedi Knight: Jedi Academy]]''</ref>

In [[12 ABY/Legends|12 ABY]], [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] hid [[Kyle Katarn]]'s lightsaber in the ruins as a test. If his skills were enough to retrieve the saber, then he would be entitled to use it.<ref name="JK:JO" /> In the same ruins Kyle later dueled dark Jedi [[Desann]]. Two years later Katarn would once again return and use the ruins to train other students, including [[Jaden Korr]] and [[Rosh Penin]].<ref name="JK:JA" />

